  "id": "7616957612126522638",
  "text": "High cortisol levels can negatively affect the body over time. Cortisol is a stress hormone released by the adrenal glands, and while it helps regulate energy and metabolism, chronically high levels can lead to problems like increased belly fat, muscle breakdown, poor sleep, and higher blood pressure. Long-term stress, lack of sleep, and overtraining can all contribute to elevated cortisol, which is why recovery, proper nutrition, and rest are important for overall health and performance.#gym #bodybuilding #fitness #gymtok #fyp ",
