{
  "id": "7615259922820762894",
  "text": "what helped me balance my hormones: \n\n1. balancing blood sugar! unregulated insulin creates a lot of the symptoms associated with PCOS. I take ACV shots before meals & use supplements like chromium, inositol, & berberine to manage insulin levels. \n\n2. Glow culture supplement: this powerful 3–in-1 supplement reduced my painful PMS symptoms, cleared my hormonal acne, & reduced my daily bloat!! Glow culture also helps balance cortisol which is a huge trigger for my PCOS. I feel calmer & more balanced on a daily basis ✨\n\n3. Moving your body daily: 10K steps daily + working out 3-4x a week regulates metabolism which helps you use the glucose you’re eating and triggers less insulin resistance \n\n4. Learn how to manage stress better & regulate nervous system: this is a life long journey! Some habits that help me lower stress are morning affirmations, yoga & stretching, myofascial release, meditation, journaling, going for walks, spending time with safe people \n\n5. Eating high fat high protein: 30g+ of protein at every meal especially breakfast! Starting the day off with protein keeps your blood sugar balanced and you fuller for longer. Insulin is the most sensitive in the mornings so it’s so important to not skip breakfast but to also eat high protein, high fat instead of high carb 🤍\n\nhope this helps xx\n\n#pcos #hormonehealth #antiinflammatory #womenshealth #hormonesupport ",
