{
  "id": "7514014067191745814",
  "text": "I haven’t shaved my legs or arm pits in 6 years.\n\nI realised I was doing because that was just the norm…\nBecause somewhere along the way, we were taught that our natural bodies aren’t good enough. \nThat smooth = feminine and hair = ugly.\nBut hair is protective with a biological function and it’s normal!\n\n🧴 Not to mention the myriad of chemicals used in shaving creams, plastic razors and lotions! \n\n🫶🏻 This isn’t to say I’m telling you to never shave again - if you genuinely want to go for it! Just ensure it’s not coming from a place of shame or “should”. \n\n🧩 Not shaving has been a little piece in my puzzle to help me reconnect to my wild natural self. \n\n#cyclesyncing #cyclicalliving #hormonehealth #naturalbeauty #dontshave #cleanbeauty #toxicfreeliving #wildfeminine #nervoussystemhealing #rootcausehealing #ancestralhealth #holistichealing #radicalselfcare #selfsovereignty #ditchthetoxins #bodyliteracy #metabolichealth #feminineenergy #nontoxicskincare #hormonebalance #periodhealth #womenwiththewild #beautyfromwithin #rewildyourself #consciousliving #naturalhairgrowth #wombwisdom #holisticliving #slowlivingmovement #femininebodywisdom",
