{
  "id": "7585636021459553550",
  "text": "I used to feel so much guilt about never initiating.\n\nEspecially because my partner told me it was something he wanted more of.\n\nEvery time the topic came up, my chest would tighten.\n\nI wanted to try…\n\nBut I just didn’t feel the spark out of nowhere. I didn’t want to force it.\n\nS*ggs was never on my mind.\n\nAnd I started to feel like maybe I just wasn’t attracted to my partner.\n\nOr maybe there was something wrong with me.\n\nAnd when I tried to initiate harder when I didn’t feel like it, I ended up being more resentful and shut down.\n\nHere’s what I wish I knew sooner…\n\nI don’t initiate because I have responsive desire.\n\nFor me and 85% of women, we don’t often experience that spontaneous urge out of the blue. \n\nWe need time, touch, pleasure, and the right context to feel desire.\n\nWe feel desire AFTER intimacy starts. \n\nSo the solution that works for me is scheduling intimacy.\n\nThat gives me time to prepare, warm up, turn myself on, and get excited for my partner.\n\nHe feels wanted and prioritized, and my responsive desire has time to get online.\n\nThis is the power of knowing your body and what turns you on.\n\n#relationshipadvice #intimacy ",
