  "id": "7471015985248783662",
  "text": "Low libido in women (especially those aged 35-55) is often linked to a combination of hormonal imbalances, stress, and poor metabolic health. \n\nHere are some reasons why you may have low libido…\n\n        •.      Low Testosterone: Women need testosterone for libido, muscle tone, and motivation. Declining levels (especially in perimenopause) can reduce desire.\n\t•\tLow Estrogen: Estrogen keeps vaginal tissues lubricated and supports mood. A drop (common in perimenopause and menopause) can cause dryness and discomfort.\n\t•\tHigh Cortisol (Chronic Stress): When cortisol is high, the body prioritizes survival over reproduction, leading to low libido.\n\t•\tLow Progesterone: Progesterone has a calming effect; low levels (common with stress and perimenopause) can lead to anxiety and lower sex drive.\n\n       • Insulin Resistance: Fluctuating blood sugar levels lead to energy crashes, cravings, and poor circulation—all of which can impact libido.\n\t•\tLow Thyroid Function: Hypothyroidism slows metabolism, causes fatigue, and can lower sex drive.\n\n        •.    Leaky Gut & Dysbiosis: An imbalanced gut can lead to systemic inflammation, impacting hormones and neurotransmitters like dopamine and serotonin (which influence libido).\n\nIf you are suffering with low libido and it’s affecting your relationship, send me a private DM or book a free call on my website:\nWww.theoptimalhealthsolution.com\n\nI would love to help you get your libido back and feel sexy AF in your body.\n\n#libido #libidoboosting #libidoboostingtips ",
