{
  "id": "7562267050656189710",
  "text": "What questions do you have?  Another day living with lichen sclerosis 🫢 back for my annual Mona Lisa Laser Treatment to help with my symptoms from my chronic vulvar condition. \n\nMonaLisa Touch is a fractional CO2 laser treatment that uses laser energy to stimulate collagen production and tissue regeneration in the vulva and vagina, showing promise as a secondary treatment for lichen sclerosus (LS) by reducing inflammation, itching, and burning. \n\nWhile potent corticosteroid creams are the established first-line treatment for LS, the laser offers a hormone-free, non-invasive option with minimal side effects and excellent results for many patients, though more treatments than for other conditions may be needed.\n\nPersonally I noticed the difference in coloration, moisture, and texture after healing from my procedures. This will be my fourth round! #womenshealth #fyp #womenshealthmatters #lichensclerosis #obgyn",
